b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1333196\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:632:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been keeping up with our blog posts of late, you may have noticed an extra addition to our notes for last week&#8217;s maintenance release: WordPress 4.5 is now the minimum officially supported WordPress version for The Events Calendar, Events Calendar PRO, Event Tickets, Community Events, and GigPress. A minimum WordPress version of 4.4 or higher&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-wordpress-4-4/\">The Events Calendar &#038; WordPress 4.4+</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Caroline\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5988:\"<p>If you&#8217;ve been keeping up with our blog posts of late, you may have noticed an extra addition to our notes for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">last week&#8217;s maintenance release</a>: <strong>WordPress 4.5 is now the minimum officially supported WordPress version </strong>for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\">Events Calendar PRO</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/\">Community Events</a>, and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/gigpress/\">GigPress</a>. A minimum WordPress version of 4.4 or higher is now required for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/\">Filter Bar</a>, as well.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll see this change being applied to our other free and premium plugins in the coming weeks.</p>\n<h3>Why the Change?</h3>\n<p>For quite some time now, we&#8217;ve supported older versions of WordPress dating as far back as version 3.9, which was originally released in April of 2014. In software development terms, three years represents a <em>considerable</em> span of time, and we&#8217;ve seen quite a few significant releases from the WordPress community since! Adjusting our expectations for a minimum supported version of WordPress comes with a number of benefits for not just our development team, but for our user community as a whole.</p>\n<h4>Greater Stability</h4>\n<p>Keeping your site current with recent WordPress updates will provide you with access to important fixes and security improvements from the open-source WordPress community. These changes help to keep your site running smoothly and afford extra protection from hacks and exploits, so they&#8217;re definitely worth considering for all users.</p>\n<h4>Improved Compatibility</h4>\n<p>Moving to a minimum supported WordPress version of 4.5 keeps The Events Calendar and its related plugins in step with other popular plugin offerings, such as WooCommerce (which carries a minimum requirement of version 4.4) and Jetpack (which requires at least WordPress 4.7).</p>\n<p>Keeping your WordPress install up to date ensures that you&#8217;ll have access to the latest and greatest versions of all of these plugins as they become available. And while compatibility between plugins isn&#8217;t always a sure thing, you&#8217;re more likely to have a smooth experience with plugins targeted for the same or similar WordPress versions.</p>\n<h4>Sharpened Support</h4>\n<p>Reducing the number of versions that we support allows us to better target our efforts when users report issues in our forums. By moving to a more recent version of WordPress, you&#8217;ll be joining the largest portion of our user base on a more stable platform &#8211; and you&#8217;ll reap the benefits in the form of better, more focused support from our team.</p>\n<h4>Resource Efficiency</h4>\n<p>Focusing our development efforts towards more recent versions of WordPress frees up development and QA resources that would otherwise be spent ensuring broad compatibility with outdated software. This means that more of our efforts can be applied to improvements that matter to <em>you</em>, like bug fixes and feature additions.</p>\n<h4>Who’s Affected?</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re already running our plugins on a WordPress version of 4.5 or newer, you can rest easy regarding these changes. Users of current WordPress architectures who are moving to the latest versions of our plugins shouldn&#8217;t notice any differences in our update or installation processes.</p>\n<p>Any users remaining on older WordPress platforms will see an incompatibility notice when attempting to install the latest version of The Events Calendar, Event Tickets, or GigPress from the WordPress plugin directory.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1338864\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated.png\" alt=\"Notice that displays when attempting to install The Events Calendar on an older unsupported version of WordPress\" width=\"533\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated.png 533w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-140x69.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-300x147.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-430x211.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-460x225.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2017/08/tec_incompatible_version_annotated-500x245.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" /></p>\n<p>Versions of our plugins that require WordPress 4.4 or above can still generally be installed on earlier versions of WordPress. However, please be aware that problems may result that our support team would be unable to assist with.</p>\n<p>We hope this post helps to clarify our thinking in reaching this decision. We truly believe this move represents a positive step forward for our continued development efforts as well as the needs of our user base.</p>\n<p>With these changes in place, we&#8217;ll be better equipped to focus our efforts where they count: on crafting solid code and implementing great new features to make your projects even better.</p>\n<p>On behalf of all of us on the team, thanks so much for your continued support!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-events-calendar-wordpress-4-4/\">The Events Calendar &#038; WordPress 4.4+</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 24 Aug 2017 21:58:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1338531\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:652:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the sixteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.11&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Victor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8413:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the sixteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.11</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.16</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events 4.5.5</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#gp\">GigPress 2.3.19</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.11</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Avoid Event Aggregator previews or scheduled imports being marked as failures</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed start and end date limit parsing for events archive in the REST API code</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue with <samp>tribe_events_get_the_excerpt()</samp> returning a read more link that sometimes pointed to the current page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed Post ID not being sent to the_title filter for Organizers and Venues (props Anna L.)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where Month View tooltips would often go off-screen in some smaller viewport sizes</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue that would sometimes render Event Aggregator options invalid even with a valid license</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issue where the mobile.php template file would often fail to include an event&#8217;s featured image</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved issue where invalid linked post IDs prevent proper updates on linked posts (props to Mathew L. and a few others for highlighting this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Do not hijack the blog when the main events page is configured to appear on the site&#8217;s homepage (our thanks to Jason and others for flagging this problem)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; remove extra trailing double-quotes at the end of the timepicker data-format attributes</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed an issues where Event Aggregator scheduled imports could not run other than manually</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure valid license keys save as expected</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removing WP Plugin API result adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent stray commas from showing up for some event venues in the List View</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevent stray commas from showing up for some event venues in the Day View</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Modify certain event queries to widen the window of opportunity for query caching (props @garretjohnson)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve Event Aggregator message regarding Facebook token expiration</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Support importing from URLs (Event Aggregator) where the protocol hasn&#8217;t been specified by defaulting to HTTP</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed WP API adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_aggregator_meta_source</samp> to filter the Event Aggregator import source</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_events_linked_post_meta_values_{$current_linked_post_meta_key}</samp> for filtering the array of values retrieved for a specific linked post meta field</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updated views: <samp>src/views/day/single-event.php</samp> and <samp>src/views/list/single-event.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; Improvements to various strings to improve ease of translation (props to @ramiy)</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 5 new strings added, 56 updated, 1 fuzzied, and 3 obsoleted [the-events-calendar]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.16</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Added ability to filter events by location through WP_Query arguments <samp>tribe_geoloc</samp>, <samp>tribe_geoloc_lat</samp>, and <samp>tribe_geoloc_lng</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Restored functionality to Map View and location search, which were both failing under certain circumstances with certain venues</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Lock down the low-risk queries for posterity in Tribe__Events__Pro__Geo_Loc with $wpdb->prepare</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Recurrence bug with updating weekly rules, used w date format instead of N</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Enqueue the Minical Widget&#8217;s stylesheet and scripts in the <samp>&#x3C;head&#x3E;</samp> when possible</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added default highlight color for featured events in the Advanced List Widget (thank you @jhoughton1 and @solel for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed translation issue with custom fields label on event editor page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improve accuracy of &#8220;Next Events&#8221; link on single-venue pages, so that it only shows when there are truly more events to see</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed issue where the Google Maps script and its Geolocation script would load on events archive views (other than Map View) even when the &#8220;Hide location search&#8221; option was checked (thanks to Teresa A.)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added per-event CSS class in Week view, it indexes how many events start at the same time allowing unique CSS for each</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; New hook: <samp>tribe_geoloc_pre_get_venues_in_geofence</samp> for circumventing get_venues_in_geofence database query</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; New hooks: <samp>tribe_events_single_venue_posts_per_page</samp> and <samp>tribe_venue_upcoming_events</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updated views: <samp>src/views/pro/list/venue-nav.php</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 6 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [tribe-events-calendar-pro]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed WP API adjustments</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 18 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [event-tickets]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events 4.5.5</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Set the Show Map and Show Map Link fields to true by default, restoring the behavior from past versions</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fixed some typos that would sometimes show up in the Organizer selection fields</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter: <samp>tribe_events_community_apply_map_defaults</samp> for filtering venue map fields</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 28 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted [tribe-events-community]</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"gp\">GigPress 2.3.19</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter <samp>gigpress_related_post_types</samp> to allow more than just &#8220;post&#8221; for related posts</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.5</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.4.3</li>\n<li>Event Tickets Plus 4.5.3</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-21-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 21 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Hotfix – The Events Calendar 4.5.10.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-10-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 16 Aug 2017 22:02:21 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1336385\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:629:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce that The Events Calendar 4.5.10.1 is now available, resolving a set of user interface breakages (for some of our users datepickers and other selectors were not functioning correctly). Automated updates via your WordPress dashboard should be available now and you can also download the latest release directly. Thank you for your&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-10-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; The Events Calendar 4.5.10.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:870:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce that <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\">The Events Calendar 4.5.10.1</a> is now available, resolving a set of user interface breakages (for some of our users datepickers and other selectors were not functioning correctly). </p>\n<p>Automated updates via your WordPress dashboard should be available now and you can also download the <a href=\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/the-events-calendar.4.5.10.1.zip\" target=\"_blank\">latest release directly</a>. </p>\n<p>Thank you for your support and patience while we worked on this fix!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-10-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; The Events Calendar 4.5.10.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 7 August 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-7-august-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 09 Aug 2017 14:05:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1332078\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:661:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the fifteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.10 Community&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-7-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 7 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6111:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the fifteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar<strong> 4.5.10 </strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events <strong>4.5.4</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h5><strong>Note</strong>: WordPress 4.4 is the <strong><em>minimum</em></strong> officially supported version of WordPress for The Events Calendar and Community Events</h5>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.10</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Avoid duplicate events when importing from some iCal, Google Calendar and Facebook feeds in Event Aggregator (our thanks to Jason Sears, controlyours and many other users for highlighting these issues)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed bug that caused scheduled imports to get stuck in a perpetual state of failure when receiving error messages from the Event Aggregator service (our thanks to Antonio Jose and others for flagging this problem)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolved issue where errors from the Event Aggregator service were not properly logging/visible on the History tab</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved compatibility when using a non-default plugins directory including mu-plugins (our thanks to @squirrelandnnuts for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Made JSON LD permalinks overridable by all post types, so they can be filtered</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve integration with the plugins API/add new plugins screen (our thanks to David Sharpe for highlighting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve the Select2 search experience (props to @fabianmarz)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Made linked post fields&#8217; auto-save features more stringently check for empty values to prevent the plugin from trying to &#8220;save&#8221; empty values (our thanks to Jean-Marie for highlighting this problem)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Moved the organizer e-mail address field label a bit to better accommodate Community Events</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filter to <samp>tribe_get_display_end_date()</samp>&#8216;s return value</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Avoid notice-level errors while processing queues within Event Aggregator (our thanks to David Sharpe and others for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve compatibility and avoid Javascript errors when running alongside Twenty Seventeen</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.4</li>\n<li><strong>Language (The Events Calendar)</strong> &#8211; 1 new strings added, 119 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n<li><strong>Language (Common Library)</strong> &#8211; 0 new strings added, 312 updated, 1 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events 4.5.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fix a conflict with the WP Edit plugin to ensure its &#8220;disable wpautop&#8221; option does not break the Community Events submission form (our thanks to Karen for highlighting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Hide delete button for event recurrence rules</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent a notice level error occurring when the edit page is accessed while the Divi theme is in use</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Add some responsive styling to account for a wide table on the My List page (our thanks to Iwan for flagging this problem)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Added support for venue meta fields to front-end venue editor (thanks to Mario for flagging this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed bug that erroneously showed the fields for a new linked post when there was an submission error</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Enhance submission form labels for taxonomy fields so they use the real taxonomy name, not &#8220;categories&#8221; generically (our thanks to Hans-Gerd for bringing our attention to this issue)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Merged date format settings with The Events Calendar, can now be found in WP Admin &gt; Settings &gt; Display</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Add some UI to the &#8220;Timezone&#8221; selection field on the submission form to help clarify that it can be edited</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added helper text to Admin settings clarifying that subscribers can only edit/remove their own submissions</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added styling for themes like Genesis that put too much padding in the datepicker</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Enhance submission form labels for taxonomy fields so they use the real taxonomy name, not &#8220;categories&#8221; generically</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility</strong> &#8211; Minimum supported version of WordPress is now 4.4</li>\n<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; 4 new strings added, 119 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 3 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Events Calendar PRO</li>\n<li>Filter Bar</li>\n<li>Event Tickets</li>\n<li>Event Tickets Plus</li>\n<li>Community Tickets</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets</li>\n<li>Image Widget</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus</li>\n<li>GigPress</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-7-august-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 7 August 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"Release: Filter Bar 4.5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-filter-bar-4-5/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 01 Aug 2017 16:35:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1328138\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:590:\"<p>We’ve freshened up Filter Bar in version 4.5! In this release, we have focused our efforts displaying multiple filters selected to the user, showing better relationships between child categories, and some design improvements.. Changelogs for Filter Bar Ready to explore the details of this release? On to the changelogs! Fix — added class to checkbox&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-filter-bar-4-5/\">Release: Filter Bar 4.5</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2244:\"<p>We’ve freshened up Filter Bar in version 4.5! In this release, we have focused our efforts displaying multiple filters selected to the user, showing better relationships between child categories, and some design improvements..</p>\n<h3>Changelogs for Filter Bar</h3>\n<p>Ready to explore the details of this release? On to the changelogs!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — added class to checkbox items to better show parent, child, and grandparent relationship</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — display active filters selected in the Filter Bar</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — autocheck categories under parent when checked and in dropdown display all events under a parent category</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — added an upgrade script to change from autocomplete to Multi-Select</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — issue where only the first event would show when using State/Province, City, or Country filters in checkbox mode</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Select2 to replace Chosen script for dropdowns and autocomplete</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — improve horizontal filter icon styles by moving to the right of the filter names</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — reverse color scheme on vertical filter bar to make header and footer darker</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — add autocomplete to dropdowns and rename Autocomplete to Multi-Select to clarify the different selection options</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — set Events Calendar PRO&#8217;s Additional Fields filter to use alphabetical order</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added filters: <samp>tribe_events_filter_event_category_display_class</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Changed views: <samp>filter-bar/filter-view-horizontal, filter-bar/filter-view-vertical</samp></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Thanks for your continued support! We hope this update makes your sites much better, your jobs way easier, and your overall experience using our plugins a breeze. Cheers to you on behalf of everyone here at Modern Tribe!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-filter-bar-4-5/\">Release: Filter Bar 4.5</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"Hotfix – Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-eventbrite-tickets-4-4-7-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 30 Jul 2017 16:02:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1328111\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:594:\"<p>We are pleased to announce that Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1 is now available. If you have a valid license key in place then you should be able to take advantage of automated updates for this release. Alternatively, you can grab the latest version from the My Account &#8594; Downloads page. This release resolves a problem whereby&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-eventbrite-tickets-4-4-7-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1227:\"<p>We are pleased to announce that <strong>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1</strong> is now available.</p>\n<p>If you have a valid license key in place then you should be able to take advantage of automated updates for this release. Alternatively, you can grab the latest version from the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/my-account/downloads/\" target=\"_blank\">My Account &rarr; Downloads</a> page.</p>\n<p>This release resolves a problem whereby the Eventbrite ticket form was not being embedded in single event posts. Our thanks to everyone who reported this, with particular <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/topic/typo-in-api-php-preventing-showing-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\">props to Nicholas</a> for flagging this early along with a solution for the problem.</p>\n<p>If you are a user of Eventbrite Tickets, we recommend updating at your earliest convenience and please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out to us on the forums if you have any questions.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-eventbrite-tickets-4-4-7-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.7.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 24 July 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-24-july-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 26 Jul 2017 20:40:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1326138\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:653:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 14th Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar Events Calendar&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-24-july-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 24 July 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5970:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the 14th Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ct\">Community Tickets</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"“#eb&quot;\">Eventbrite Tickets</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Send Aggregator callback URL with correct Scheme</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Scheduled Aggregator cron for inserting will re-enqueue to complete scheduled imports</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid overwriting Venues and Organizers when importing FB events with similarly named Venues and Organizers</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improve handling of large and/or slow Google Calendar and iCal feeds</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid accidental overwrite of options when settings are saved in a multisite context</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Cleanup logic responsible for handling the default country option and remove confusing translation calls (our thanks to Oliver for flagging this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added period &#8220;.&#8221; separator to datepicker formats</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Avoid noise relating to PUE checks during WP CLI requests</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added tribe_events_month_get_events_in_month filter to allow overriding of events used in month templates.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar Pro</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Box-sizing issue with mini calendar widget on some themes. Thanks to @schreml for reporting this.</li>\n<li><strong>Add</strong> Action hooks before and after recurring meta fields.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improved get_ticket_counts() to account for tickets with global stock enabled</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improved <samp>tribe_events_count_available_tickets()</samp> to account for tickets with global stock enabled (thanks to Florian for reporting this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some PHP notices that would show up when buying EDD tickets.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid accidental overwrite of options when settings are saved in a multisite context</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Cleanup logic responsible for handling the default country option and remove confusing translation calls (our thanks to Oliver for flagging this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added period &#8220;.&#8221; separator to datepicker formats</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Avoid noise relating to PUE checks during WP CLI requests</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fixed some included files&#8217; paths to ensure they can be overwritten in line with our Themer&#8217;s Guide.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed some PHP notices that would show up when buying EDD tickets.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"“eb”\">Eventbrite Tickets</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Include organizer description on import from Eventbrite and sync description first with other attributes</li>\n<li><strong>New</strong> — New filter to specify in which Eventbrite API statuses an imported event&#8217;s ticket form should never show: <samp>tribe_events_eventbrite_hide_iframe_statuses</samp>t</li>\n<li><strong>New</strong> — New filter for customizing what Eventbrite API statuses are considered &#8220;Live&#8221; statuses: <samp>tribe_events_eventbrite_live_statuses</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Ensure that *all* available Eventbrite API statuses are usable for imported events, instead of just &#8220;Live&#8221; and &#8220;Draft&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Ensure that the full-sized featured image of an imported event is used, instead of a 450&#215;200 version which the API defaults to</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add a filter to disable the region not being synced with Eventbrite for venues outside of the U.S.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add a message that recurring events are not supported in the Event Series metabox of Pro</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Optimized message displayed when errors are returned from Eventbrite API (for clarity)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Do not include organizer permalink in description if organizer is imported from Eventbrite and when Pro is active</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Hide the Split Payments payment option (which only works with Ticket products) in carts that have no tickets.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ct\">Community Tickets</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Hide the Split Payments payment option (which only works with Ticket products) in carts that have no tickets.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Filter Bar</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager</li>\n<li>Image Widget</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus</li>\n<li>GigPress</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-24-july-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 24 July 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"Hotfix – The Events Calendar 4.5.8.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-8-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 21 Jul 2017 15:57:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"News & Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1324346\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:608:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce the release of The Events Calendar 4.5.8.1. This addresses an issue we identified with failing imports in our Event Aggregator code and will primarily benefit users of that service &#8212; though as ever we encourage everyone to stay up-to-date wherever possible 🙂 As usual, most users will be able to take&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-8-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; The Events Calendar 4.5.8.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Barry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1564:\"<p>We&#8217;re pleased to announce the release of <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\">The Events Calendar 4.5.8.1</a>.</p>\n<p>This addresses an issue we identified with failing imports in our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\">Event Aggregator</a> code and will primarily benefit users of that service &mdash; though as ever we encourage everyone to stay up-to-date wherever possible <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.3/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"🙂\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>As usual, most users will be able to take advantage of automated updates for this release but it is also possible to grab the latest version from the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/my-account/downloads/\" target=\"_blank\">My Account &rarr; Downloads</a> page or indeed directly from <a href=\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/the-events-calendar.4.5.8.1.zip\" target=\"_blank\">wordpress.org</a>.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your continued support and happy calendaring! If we can help with any questions relating to this release, please don&#8217;t hesitate to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/forum/events/events-calendar-pro/\" target=\"_blank\">reach out</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-the-events-calendar-4-5-8-1/\">Hotfix &#8211; The Events Calendar 4.5.8.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 10th July 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-10th-july-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 13 Jul 2017 13:56:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1319226\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:660:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the thirteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.8 Events&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-10th-july-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 10th July 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6224:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the thirteenth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.8</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.14</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ct\">Community Tickets 4.4.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=“#eb\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.6</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.8</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Remove permalink logic for recurring events (Events Calendar PRO will implement instead)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid type error when setting up one-time imports for Facebook URLs (our thanks to @J for flagging this!) </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Add a safety check in <samp>isOrganizer()</samp> function (our thanks to Kevin for flagging this!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixes to the plugin upgrade notice parser including support for environments where the data stream wrapper is unavailable</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure the multichoice settings configured to allow no selection work as expected</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Enqueue expired notice and CSS on every admin page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Allow passing multiple localize-scripts to tribe-assets. Don&#8217;t output a localized scrip more than once.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add helper to retrieve anonymous objects using the class name, hook and callback priority</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Allow <samp>dependency.js</samp> to handle radio buttons. ensure that they are linked correctly.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.14</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Do not generate exclusions for recurring events simply because the child instances have falled outside of the configured cleanup range</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Consolidate generation of /all/ and single recurring event permalink logic within Events Calendar PRO</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improve compatibility with WP SEO Premium and stop redirect rules from being generated inappropriately when recurring events are updated</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Default to showing upcoming event instances in the /all/ view (but fallback on showing expired events if no upcoming events remain in the series)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Hide others users from attendee managers email options</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — In &#8216;user event confirmations&#8217; shortcode, add shortcode name to <samp>shortcode_atts</samp> function call to give more customization options</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added a filter to modify the Primary Info column of the Attendees Table</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added a filter to hide the attendee optout option in the tickets form</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added new parameters to RSVP email filters</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixes to the plugin upgrade notice parser including support for environments where the data stream wrapper is unavailable</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure the multichoice settings configured to allow no selection work as expected</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Enqueue expired notice and CSS on every admin page</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Allow passing multiple localize-scripts to tribe-assets. Don&#8217;t output a localized scrip more than once.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Add helper to retrieve anonymous objects using the class name, hook and callback priority</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Allow <samp>dependency.js</samp> to handle radio buttons. ensure that they are linked correctly.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Adjustments to improve compatibility with WooCommerce 3.x during check-in and when sending emails</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent errors in relation to our integration with the WooCommerce email system</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Allow users to disable WooCommerce ticket emails by deselecting all trigger statuses</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Remove references to legacy plugins in the tickets form</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Remove view files from deprecated e-commerce providers</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Added a filter to hide the attendee optout option in the tickets form</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ct\">Community Tickets 4.4.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Added notice when Woo, Community, or Event Tickets is not active</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=“eb”>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.6</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Stopped using deprecated function <samp>Tribe__Events__Cost_Utils::instance()</samp></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Increased height of ticket iframe to lessen the likelihood of a scrollbar appearing</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Show message on Import page dropdown when API Key is not configured</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Default to not showing the ticket form when there are no tickets (overrideable)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.4.3</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.5.2</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.18</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-10th-july-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 10th July 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"Maintenance Release for the Week of 26th June 2017\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-26th-june-2017/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 27 Jun 2017 14:31:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1308403\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:657:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the twelfth Maintenance Release of 2017. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The Events Calendar 4.5.7 Events&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-26th-june-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 26th June 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Courtney\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7530:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the twelfth Maintenance Release of 2017. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.7</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.13</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fb\">Filter Bar 4.4.3</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.5.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ce\">Community Events 4.5.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#gp\">GigPress 2.3.18</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.5.7</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Restore support for translated events category slugs when WPML is active </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improve handling of shortcodes within event view excerpts (props: @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/awbauer\">awbauer</a>)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improve compatibility with WPML in relation to event permalinks specifically (props: @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/dgwatkins\">dgwatkins</a>) </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Improved handling of Venue fields that allows for better form validation in Community Events</li>\n<p> 	<!-- common --> </p>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Made the App Shop and help pages work on Windows. </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Resolved issue where the Meta Chunker attempted to inappropriately chunk meta for post post_types</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid notices during plugin update and installation checks</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure an empty <samp>dateTimeSeparator</samp> option value doesn&#8217;t break <samp>tribe_get_start_date</samp> output anymore.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improve navigation to elements inside admin pages (don&#8217;t let the admin toolbar obscure things)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Textual corrections (with thanks to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/garrett-eclipse\">garrett-eclipse</a></li>\n<p> <!-- end common --></p>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Better detection and reporting of communication failures with the Event Aggregator server</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Textual corrections (with thanks to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/garrett-eclipse\">garrett-eclipse</a> for highlighting many of these)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — New filter added (<samp>&#8220;tribe_events_linked_posts_dropdown_enable_creation&#8221;</samp>) to facilitate more control over linked posts</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improve performance of theme compatibility code </li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Don&#8217;t show Event Aggregator system status in Help tab if there&#8217;s no Event Aggregator license in place</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar PRO 4.4.13</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure that the necessary assets to support location-based searching are available to <samp>[tribe_events]</samp> embedded views (our thanks to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/Miroslav\">Miroslav</a> for highlighting this issue!)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Make sure that the correct date format is used and the recurrence description works for &#8220;once&#8221;-type recurrence rules (our thanks to Robert and others in the forums for flagging this)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Change how event title is generated for This Week Widget to be inline with other widgets and views</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Update the mini calendar widget events count parameter label to avoid confusion</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Never ending &#038; long term recurrence &#8220;learn more&#8221; link now points at a more helpful resource and opens up in a new window</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3>Filter Bar 4.4.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; add back markers for sorting and dropdown of the active filters in the admin</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.5.1</h3>\n<ul>\n<!-- common --> </p>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Made the App Shop and help pages work on Windows. </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Resolved issue where the Meta Chunker attempted to inappropriately chunk meta for post post_types</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Avoid notices during plugin update and installation checks</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure an empty <samp>dateTimeSeparator</samp> option value doesn&#8217;t break <samp>tribe_get_start_date</samp> output anymore.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improve navigation to elements inside admin pages (don&#8217;t let the admin toolbar obscure things)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Textual corrections (with thanks to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/garrett-eclipse\">garrett-eclipse</a></li>\n<p> <!-- end common --></p>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Spelling and related language fixes (with thanks to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/garrett-eclipse\">garrett-eclipse</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets Plus 4.5.1</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Ensure the correct user ID is associated with tickets/attendees (props: @<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/users/svkg/\">Andras</a>)</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure the <samp>event_id and ticket_id</samp> variables are usable within the <samp>tribe_tickets_plus_qr_handle_redirects</samp> filter (props: @<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/users/cliff/\">Cliff</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ce\">Community Events 4.5.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Improved handling of Venue fields that allows for better form validation in Community Events</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure the &#8220;Users cannot create new Venues|Organizers&#8221; setting is respected </li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure the <samp>tribe-no-js</samp> class is removed when appropriate</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Do not render the venue or organizer template modules if the current user can neither select nor create those posts</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"gp\">GigPress 2.3.18</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent PHP notices from appearing in log files when editing an event</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent PHP Notice when no shows are added, but multiple artists are present</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — The Show Notes field can now render shortcodes (props to @<a href=\"http://profiles.wordpress.org/cowboyofbottrop\">cowboyofbottrop</a>)</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Improvements to source code (props to @<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/leecollings\">leecollings</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.4.3</li>\n<li>Image Widget 4.4.5</li>\n<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-week-26th-june-2017/\">Maintenance Release for the Week of 26th June 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:10:{s:6:\"server\";s:5:\"nginx\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Thu, 31 Aug 2017 10:23:10 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:23:\"PHP/5.6.29-1~dotdeb+7.1\";s:4:\"vary\";s:6:\"Cookie\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"af8771888a34410ce5eb7cca3f0f4eb0\"\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"<https://theeventscalendar.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Thu, 31 Aug 2017 09:44:03 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:29:\"max-age=3600, must-revalidate\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20130911020210\";}','no'),(902,'_transient_timeout_feed_mod_0d102f2a1f4d6bc90eb8c6ffe